# An adopted recipe — a capability this repo BUILT from someone else's handover — is listed
# too, and at the version this repo actually took: hiding it would read as "nothing was ever
# handed to us", and a version-less line would leave a reader unable to tell it from stale.
exec sporo adopt handoff.md
stdout 'sporo adopt: nightly-digest 1\.0\.0 \(source: handoff\.md\)'

exec sporo list
stdout 'official daily-progress-report'
stdout 'adopted  nightly-digest \(1\.0\.0\)'

-- handoff.md --
---
name: nightly-digest
version: 1.0.0
title: A nightly digest that checks itself
---

# Nightly digest

## The problem
You do not have the thing. You have it when the check passes.
